text: Today  I am proud of myself Today  I am proud of myself With the crumbling of my relationship over the past week  my continuously building stress and panic from work  and just general feelings of failure and pain  I had a difficult interaction with someone today  I m a part of this group getting ready to climb Mount Whitney  the tallest mountain in continental United States  It s a once every few years chance kind of thing  because you need to get a permit and the permits are next to impossible to obtain  Today  the leader of the group  James  expressed doubt that I could make it  and was encouraging me to rethink going That was crushing  I already don t believe in myself  but to hear that others are doubting me too  others see me as a failure too  I can t  I can t  I was so hurt  and crushed  I didn t think I was that bad  I alternate between running three times a week and climbing the stairs machine at the gym for an hour at a time  I ve climbed mountains before  I consider myself relatively fit  But he still expressed doubt I could keep up with the group  and I just felt so crushed   I wanted to scream and get really aggressive  I wanted to get pissy and tell him he doesn t know me  I wanted to give up and say give my permit to someone else  I was feeling so many things  He could tell that I was feeling really attacked  and tension was building But I took a deep breath  and said   I m going through a hard time right now  If I seem sensitive  I want you to know it s not your fault or responsibility  If you think I can t keep up with the group  then I would be happy for a compromise  I will make my own transportation arrangements and hike at my own pace  I ll still be able to make it  but I won t be anyone s responsibility The tension immediately dissolved  I felt really proud of myself  I communicated my emotions effectively  explained why there was tension  absolved him of responsibility  and suggested a good alternative solution  I feel so out of control of my emotions all the time  it felt so good to feel in control  for once
summary: James is a member of a group getting ready to climb Mount Whitney the tallest mountain in continental United States. The leader of the group expressed doubt that James could keep up with the group and encouraged him to rethink going. James decided to compromise and make his own transportation arrangements and hike at his own pace.
